de.interactive_instruments.etf.detector

Interface TestObjectTypeDetector

  • All Superinterfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<TestObjectTypeDetector>, de.interactive_instruments.Initializable, de.interactive_instruments.Releasable

    public interface TestObjectTypeDetector
extends de.interactive_instruments.Initializable, de.interactive_instruments.Releasable, java.lang.Comparable<TestObjectTypeDetector>
    This interface is implemented by detectors that detect the Test Object Types from a resource.

    • Method Detail

      • detectType

        DetectedTestObjectType detectType(Resource resource,
                                  java.util.Set<EID> expectedTypes)
        Verify the resource is one of the passed Test Object Types and return the detected type. Otherwise return null. Note: the TestObjectTypeDetectorManager may define a timeout in future versions. A TestObjectTypeDetector should analyse the content within 5 seconds.
        Parameters:
        resource - resource the TestObjectTypeDetector must use for retrieving and analyzing content
        expectedTypes - Test Object Type ids to check
        Returns:
        detected Test Object Type or null if unknown or other type

      • detectType

        default DetectedTestObjectType detectType(Resource resource)
        Detect the Test Object Type from a resource Note: the TestObjectTypeDetectorManager may define a timeout in future versions. A TestObjectTypeDetector should analyse the content within 15 seconds.
        Parameters:
        resource - resource the TestObjectTypeDetector must use for retrieving and analyzing content
        Returns:
        detected Test Object Type or null if unknown or other type

      • getPriority

        default int getPriority()
        If multiple TestObjectTypeDetectors are registered, detectors with a higher priority are used first for detection. If two TestObjectTypeDetectors are attempting to register Test Object Types with the same EID (means it returns the types via supportedTypes()), the TestObjectTypeDetector with the higher priority will win.
        Returns:
        priority

      • supportedTypes

        EidMap<TestObjectTypeDto> supportedTypes()
        Get all types the TestObjectType detector can detect. This will register all supported types in the TestObjectTypeDetectorManager.
        Returns:
        supported test object types

        default int compareTo(TestObjectTypeDetector o)
